        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can draw text directly to the background of a control by converting a text string to a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.FormattedText&gt;</ph> object, and then drawing the object to the control's <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.DrawingContext&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can also use this technique for drawing to the background of objects derived from <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Panel&gt;</ph>, such as <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Canvas&gt;</ph> and <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">![</bpt>Controls displaying text as background<ept id="p1">]</ept><bpt id="p2">(./media/drawtext2background01.png "</bpt>DrawText2Background01<ept id="p2">")</ept></source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example of controls with custom text backgrounds</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To draw to the background of a control, create a new <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.DrawingBrush&gt;</ph> object and draw the converted text to the object's <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.DrawingContext&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Then, assign the new <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.DrawingBrush&gt;</ph> to the control's background property.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following code example shows how to create a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.FormattedText&gt;</ph> object and draw to the background of a <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Label&gt;</ph> and <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button&gt;</ph> object.</source>
